I'm Jesse, and I'm in my second year at UT Austin.

# Where did you grow up?

I grew up in a relatively large (~100,000 people) suburb of Dallas, named Richardson.
If it weren't for the University of Texas at Dallas, which is located a couple minutes from my house, you'd probably never hear of Richardson.
My dad teaches at UTD, so that's how my family ended up living there!

# Why are you majoring in CS?

I went to Richardson High School, which happened to have a really strong computer science program, and a very passionate cs teacher.
With my friends, I competed in competitive programming competitions, hackathons, and capture-the-flags (a security competition).




